<br>
At the release of Shadows of Luclic Thunder of Karana was seriously unbalanced. Three or four paladins could relatively easily shut down all special effects of  an ¡¥ueber¡¦ mob by chain casting ToK. Examples are 12 people slaying Sontalek or a Lady Vox/Gorenaire fight that was reduced to the difficult of fighting a giant in Kael. Action had to be taken quickly and the spell was changed to a mana sieve spell. <br>
<br>
Discussion of a Workable Silencing Spell<br>
<br>
The paladin community started discussing a fair replacement spell that fulfilled the original intend of the spell: to give paladins a specific raid role by granting them the ability to counter gate and complete heal spells of dragons. Dragon¡¦s AoE breath weapons and special procs should not be silenceable. <br>
<br>
We discussed different options and we came to the conclussion that only a spell that was chainable by several paladins would fulfill the hopes of us paladins. We were hoping that a raid force desired to have more than just one paladin for Divine Strength on a raid. A chainable spell would accomplish that. Secondarily, silencing a dragon for only one spell duration would only mean that a dragon would gate or complete heal after the six seconds passed. Only a chainable version of a silence spell would make a noticable but not encounter changing difference in a battle.<br>
<br>
The original spell statistics for mana, duration and recast time were perfect. Thunder of Karana would have found good but not unbalancing use in raid scenarios as well as regular fights in places like Sebilis or Karnor¡¦s Castle. The resist levels were well balanced for single or chained use of the spell. Only the inadvertant AoE breath weapon or special attack silencing has to be corrected. <br>
<br>
Implementation of a Working Silence Spell<br>
<br>
From there we discussed different implementations that would allow AoE breath weapons and procs to continue but regular spells like Complete Heal and Gates to be silenced. We understand these special attacks of dragons are coded as spells similar to any other spell.<br>
<br>
In the selection of the approach we tried to find a method that would not require extensive programming, reviewing each mob's spell selection or time intensive flagging of mobs and spells that can be silenced. Only an approach that could globally be applied and does not require review of all mobs in Everquest would be feasable. There is a general concern in the paladin community that any complex implementation would be discussed but due to time and cost issues never implemented. <br>
<br>
There are a few approaches that could be used to restrict the repertoire of a silenced dragon¡¦s spells to only AoE or proc weapons without excessive implementation cost. Restrict the spell list of a silenced dragon to only spells that:<br>
<br>
o have a cast time of less than 1 second <br>
o have zero mana cost<br>
<br>
Or alternatively lower the channeling skill of a dragon by 95% when the dragon is silenced. This would similarily to restricting the spell selection list allow fast casting AoE weapons and procs to succeed but gates and complete heals to be interrupted.<br>
<br>
We believe that the suggested implementation options would fulfill the great initial thought of  the Thunder of Karana spell and give Paladins a specific and accumulative raid role they lack so badly. The risk of introducing an unbalancing spell with this implementation is low, so is the development cost.<br>
<br>
Please consider the above thoughts. Feel free to contact me or any member of the Paladin of Norrath community for further information.<br>
<br>
